#: ../../spinningup/extra_tf_pg_implementation.rst:3
msgid "Extra Material: Tensorflow Policy Gradient Implementation Examples"
msgstr "補充材料：Tensorflow 策略梯度實作範例"

#: ../../spinningup/extra_tf_pg_implementation.rst:7
msgid "Implementing the Simplest Policy Gradient"
msgstr "實作最簡單的策略梯度"

#: ../../spinningup/extra_tf_pg_implementation.rst:9
msgid ""
"We give a short Tensorflow implementation of this simple version of the "
"policy gradient algorithm in "
"``spinup/examples/tf1/pg_math/1_simple_pg.py``. (It can also be viewed "
"`on github "
"<https://github.com/openai/spinningup/blob/master/spinup/examples/tf1/pg_math/1_simple_pg.py>`_.)"
" It is only 122 lines long, so we highly recommend reading through it in "
"depth. While we won't go through the entirety of the code here, we'll "
"highlight and explain a few important pieces."
msgstr ""
"我們在 ``spinup/examples/tf1/pg_math/1_simple_pg.py`` 中提供了此簡單版本策略梯度演算法"
"的簡短 Tensorflow 實作。（也可以在 `on github "
"<https://github.com/openai/spinningup/blob/master/spinup/examples/tf1/pg_math/1_simple_pg.py>`_ "
"上檢視。）它只有 122 行，因此我們強烈建議深入閱讀。雖然我們不會在此逐行講解所有程式碼，"
"但會重點說明幾個重要的部分。"

#: ../../spinningup/extra_tf_pg_implementation.rst:11
msgid "**1. Making the Policy Network.**"
msgstr "**1. 建構策略網路。**"

#: ../../spinningup/extra_tf_pg_implementation.rst:24
msgid ""
"This block builds a feedforward neural network categorical policy. (See "
"the `Stochastic Policies`_ section in Part 1 for a refresher.) The "
"``logits`` tensor can be used to construct log-probabilities and "
"probabilities for actions, and the ``actions`` tensor samples actions "
"based on the probabilities implied by ``logits``."
msgstr ""
"這段程式碼建構了一個前饋神經網路的類別型策略（categorical policy）。"
"（可參閱第一部分的 `Stochastic Policies`_ 章節複習。）``logits`` 張量可用於建構動作的"
"對數機率和機率，而 ``actions`` 張量則根據 ``logits`` 所隱含的機率來採樣動作。"

#: ../../spinningup/extra_tf_pg_implementation.rst:28
msgid "**2. Making the Loss Function.**"
msgstr "**2. 建構損失函數。**"

#: ../../spinningup/extra_tf_pg_implementation.rst:42
msgid ""
"In this block, we build a \"loss\" function for the policy gradient "
"algorithm. When the right data is plugged in, the gradient of this loss "
"is equal to the policy gradient. The right data means a set of (state, "
"action, weight) tuples collected while acting according to the current "
"policy, where the weight for a state-action pair is the return from the "
"episode to which it belongs. (Although as we will show in later "
"subsections, there are other values you can plug in for the weight which "
"also work correctly.)"
msgstr ""
"在這段程式碼中，我們為策略梯度演算法建構了一個「損失」函數。當輸入正確的資料時，"
"此損失的梯度等於策略梯度。所謂正確的資料是指按照當前策略行動時收集的一組"
"（狀態、動作、權重）元組，其中狀態-動作對的權重是其所屬回合（episode）的回報。"
"（不過正如我們將在後續小節中展示的，還有其他可以作為權重的值同樣適用。）"

#: ../../spinningup/extra_tf_pg_implementation.rst:45
#: ../../spinningup/extra_tf_pg_implementation.rst:60
msgid "You Should Know"
msgstr "你應該知道"

#: ../../spinningup/extra_tf_pg_implementation.rst:47
msgid ""
"Even though we describe this as a loss function, it is **not** a loss "
"function in the typical sense from supervised learning. There are two "
"main differences from standard loss functions."
msgstr ""
"儘管我們將其描述為損失函數，但它**並非**監督式學習中典型意義的損失函數。"
"與標準損失函數有兩個主要差異。"

#: ../../spinningup/extra_tf_pg_implementation.rst:49
msgid ""
"**1. The data distribution depends on the parameters.** A loss function "
"is usually defined on a fixed data distribution which is independent of "
"the parameters we aim to optimize. Not so here, where the data must be "
"sampled on the most recent policy."
msgstr ""
"**1. 資料分佈取決於參數。** 損失函數通常定義在一個固定的資料分佈上，"
"且該分佈與我們要最佳化的參數無關。但這裡並非如此，資料必須從最新的策略中採樣。"

#: ../../spinningup/extra_tf_pg_implementation.rst:51
#, python-brace-format
msgid ""
"**2. It doesn't measure performance.** A loss function usually evaluates "
"the performance metric that we care about. Here, we care about expected "
"return, :math:`J(\\pi_{\\theta})`, but our \"loss\" function does not "
"approximate this at all, even in expectation. This \"loss\" function is "
"only useful to us because, when evaluated at the current parameters, with"
" data generated by the current parameters, it has the negative gradient "
"of performance."
msgstr ""
"**2. 它不衡量性能。** 損失函數通常評估我們關心的性能指標。在這裡，我們關心的是"
"期望回報 :math:`J(\\pi_{\\theta})`，但我們的「損失」函數完全不近似它，"
"即使在期望值上也不是。這個「損失」函數之所以有用，僅僅是因為在當前參數下、"
"使用當前參數生成的資料來評估時，它具有性能的負梯度。"

#: ../../spinningup/extra_tf_pg_implementation.rst:53
msgid ""
"But after that first step of gradient descent, there is no more "
"connection to performance. This means that minimizing this \"loss\" "
"function, for a given batch of data, has *no* guarantee whatsoever of "
"improving expected return. You can send this loss to :math:`-\\infty` and"
" policy performance could crater; in fact, it usually will. Sometimes a "
"deep RL researcher might describe this outcome as the policy "
"\"overfitting\" to a batch of data. This is descriptive, but should not "
"be taken literally because it does not refer to generalization error."
msgstr ""
"但在梯度下降的第一步之後，就不再與性能有任何關聯了。這意味著對於給定的一批資料，"
"最小化這個「損失」函數*完全不保證*能改善期望回報。你可以把損失降到 :math:`-\\infty`，"
"而策略的性能可能會急劇下降；實際上通常確實如此。有時深度強化學習研究者會將這種結果"
"描述為策略對一批資料「過擬合」。這種說法有描述性，但不應照字面理解，"
"因為它並不是指泛化誤差。"

#: ../../spinningup/extra_tf_pg_implementation.rst:55
msgid ""
"We raise this point because it is common for ML practitioners to "
"interpret a loss function as a useful signal during training---\"if the "
"loss goes down, all is well.\" In policy gradients, this intuition is "
"wrong, and you should only care about average return. The loss function "
"means nothing."
msgstr ""
"我們提出這點是因為機器學習從業者通常會將損失函數解讀為訓練過程中的有用信號——"
"「如果損失下降了，一切都很好。」在策略梯度中，這種直覺是錯誤的，"
"你應該只關注平均回報。損失函數沒有任何意義。"

#: ../../spinningup/extra_tf_pg_implementation.rst:62
msgid ""
"The approach used here to make the ``log_probs`` tensor---creating an "
"action mask, and using it to select out particular log "
"probabilities---*only* works for categorical policies. It does not work "
"in general."
msgstr ""
"這裡用於建構 ``log_probs`` 張量的方法——建立動作遮罩（action mask）並用它來選取"
"特定的對數機率——*僅*適用於類別型策略（categorical policy），不適用於一般情況。"

#: ../../spinningup/extra_tf_pg_implementation.rst:66
msgid "**3. Running One Epoch of Training.**"
msgstr "**3. 執行一個訓練週期。**"

